[normal]International Service is a development organisation that has been changing lives for the better for more than 60 years by empowering some of the 
[normal]world’s poorest and most marginalised people.
[normal]Our international programmes are in West Africa, Latin America and the occupied Palestinian territory where social and economic inclusion for all people is central to our work.
[normal]International Service’s developme
[normal]nt
[normal] 
[normal]workers support local project partners
[normal] 
[normal]with specialist skills and knowledge so
[normal] 
[normal]that they and their organisations grow
[normal] 
[normal]in effectiveness and impact.
[normal]Our work is also about influencing the development and delivery
[normal] 
[normal]of human rights policies in the countries 
[normal]where we operate on
[normal] 
[normal]behalf of vulnerable and excluded groups of people.
[normal]International Service is currently part of the consortium of agencies delivering the International Citizenship
[normal] Service (ICS) 
[normal]funded through DFID.
[normal]Our inclusion programme has a focus on
[normal] disability and we also work with disability projects as part of our work within the ICS programme. 
[normal]Further information on International Service and our work can be found at 
[normal]www.internationalservice.org.
